Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The Central Business Park is a well-located development within close proximity to Bournemouth Town Centre and the main A338 Wessex Way dual carriage way, providing quick and easy access to the wider Bournemouth, Christchurch and Poole conurbation. The property is located approx. 1. mile east of the St Pauls roundabout, Bournemouth Mainline Railway Station and Asda Superstore. 

The property is a modern detached unit of steel portal frame construction and benefits from securely fenced and gated yard area. The ground floor warehouse / industrial area is accessed through a dock level internal loading bay area (via 3no large loading doors) from the main yard area and one additional ground level loading door from the northern elevation. The ground and first floor offices provide refurbished accommodation and there are WC facilities on both floors.

St. Modwen Park Poole is in the process of seeking detailed planning consent to accommodate up to 191,000 sq ft of warehouse space in three units. The units are planned to be speculatively constructed, delivering a scheme of units ranging from 40,000 sq ft up to 105,000 sq ft. Construction is due to start April 2020 with units ready for occupation in February 2021. 

St Modwen Park is prominently located at the head of Sterte Avenue, overlooking the A350 (Holes Bay Road). Holes Bay Road provides access to A35 heading west, the A350 heading north and the A3049 to the east which provides access to Junction 1 of the M27 via the A348 and A31. Major occupiers in close proximity to St Modwen Park include Mercedes Benz of Poole, Premier Inn Hotel, Sunseeker, Lush and Addo Food Group. 

The site is also in close proximity to Wessex Gate Retail Park. Poole town centre and Poole Station are located 0.5 miles to the south providing direct access to London Waterloo. Bournemouth Airport is located approximately 9 miles to the North East.

Aviation Business Park is a well-established and successful business destination in the South Coast region currently supporting over 200 individual businesses in a range of mixed-use accommodation. It has a strong reputation as a key specialist aerospace and manufacturing hub for companies looking for bespoke and high-specification facilities to help them deliver their specific and quality products and services.

ABP21 is a substantially refurbished 21,421 sq ft industrial/warehouse unit at Bournemouth Airport.

110 minutes to London by train

23 direct flights to Europe

100miles to London

15 minutes to town centre by bus

90 minutes the M25 by car

Aviation Business Park is a well-established and successful business destination in the South Coast Region. Supporting over 200 individual businesses in a range of mixed-use accommodation, Aviation Business Park has developed a strong reputation as a key specialist aerospace and manufacturing hub for companies looking for bespoke and high specification facilities.

ABP39 is a 39,124 sq ft high specification industrial warehouse opportunity, designed as a detached unit with steel clad pitched roof incorporating daylight panels, profiled steel cladding, power floated concrete factory/warehouse floor and double-glazed windows at ground and first floor level. The first floor office will benefit from a carpeted open plan theme with central heating and a suspended ceiling incorporating recessed lighting.

Travel Distances:

+ 110 minutes to London by train

+ 23 direct flights to Europe

+ 100miles to London

+ 15 minutes to town centre by bus

+ 90 minutes the M25 by car

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Aviation Business Park is situated only 5 miles north of Bournemouth, 1 mile west of the A338 and 100 miles south west of London. It can be accessed via the A31 from the M27 and M3 motorway to the east, and via the A35 to the west and excellent road links mean the journey time from the M25 to Bournemouth Airport can be as little as 75 minutes.

Building 107D offers 5,741 sq ft (534 sq m) plus 5,647 sq ft (451 sq m) concrete mezzanine.

Location

Aviation Business Park is situated only 5 miles north of Bournemouth, 1 mile west of the A338 and 100 miles south west of London. It can be accessed via the A31 from the M27 and M3 motorway to the east, and via the A35 to the west and excellent road links mean the journey time from the M25 to Bournemouth Airport can be as little as 75 minutes.

Building 397A offers 3,985 sq. ft.

Description

+ Detached blister building with yard
+ Electricity
+ Strip lighting
+ Concrete floor
+ Loading door measuring 4.2m x 4.2m
+ Kitchenette
+ Use of shared male and female WC facilities
+ Approx. 0.1 acre yard/parking
+ EPC D 81

The property is located in the south-east sector of Bournemouth Airport close to the terminal building. The A338 Wessex Way which provides dual carriageway links into Bournemouth and the A31 is approximately 2 miles distant.

These end of terrace premises are of steel portal frame construction with composite cladding. The ground floor is concrete, the internal eaves height is approximately 5.89 metres and loading is by way of a sectional up and over door measuring approximately 4.4 metres wide x 4.89 metres high.

A separate personnel door leads to the ground floor office accommodation which is arranged as five offices with female/disabled and male cloakroom facilities and a kitchenette. In the factory area, there is a fluorescent strip lighting and steel stairs lead to a first floor concrete mezzanine.

3 phase electricity is connected.

Externally there are tarmacadam and concrete forecourts providing parking.

The premises are arranged as Hangar 401, Building 401A and Offices/Stores.

Hangar 401
Hangar 401 has steel clad elevations with a pitched steel-clad roof incorporating daylight panels. The floor is concrete, there are low bay lights and there are 3 No. electric roller doors measuring approximately 4.89m wide x 5m high, 3.89m wide x 3.94m high and 3.9m wide x 5m high. There are windows in the upper side elevation, the clear internal height is 6.5m and the internal eaves height is 10.6m. There is an oil-fired warm air heater and there is 3 phase electricity.

Building 401A
Building 401A is a link building to the side of Hangar 401 and has a concrete floor (raised in parts along the side elevation), a steel-clad roof incorporating daylight panels, an internal eaves height of 6.4m and brick/steel cladding. There is a personnel door, a gas fired warm heater and fluorescent strip lighting.

Offices/Stores
This section is single storey with brick elevations, a pitched roof and windows. Internally, there is a kitchenette, male and female WCs, carpeted offices with a suspended ceiling incorporating recessed lighting and a storage area with vinyl flooring.

Aviation Business Park is situated only 5 miles north of Bournemouth, 1 mile west of the A338 and 100 miles south west of London. It can be accessed via the A31 from the M27 and M3 motorway to the east, and via the A35 to the west and excellent road links mean the journey time from the M25 to Bournemouth Airport can be as little as 75 minutes.

Unit 3 offers 1,691 sq. ft and Unit 4 offers 2,121 sq. ft. Both are available from April 2021.

UNIT 3 SPECIFICATION:

- Internal height 3.2m
- Carpeted office
- Concrete floor
- Double wooden loading doors (2.4m w x 2.7m h)
- Male and female WCs
- UPVC windows and personnel door in front elevation
- Single phase electricity
- Car Parking
- EPC Rating E 105

UNIT 4 SPECIFICATION:

- Suspended ceiling (to part)
- Carpeted office accommodation
- Kitchen/break out area
- 3 no. patitioned offices
- Male and female WCs
- UPVC windows and personnel door in front elevation
- 3 phase electricity is available
- Car Parking
- EPC Rating E 121
